Class AccordionWrap<CONTROL extends javafx.scene.control.Accordion>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.jemmy.control.ScreenArea, org.jemmy.interfaces.ControlInterface, org.jemmy.interfaces.Focusable, org.jemmy.interfaces.KeyTarget, org.jemmy.interfaces.MouseTarget

    @ControlType(value=javafx.scene.control.Accordion.class)
@ControlInterfaces(value={org.jemmy.interfaces.Selectable.class,org.jemmy.interfaces.Selectable.class},
                   encapsulates={java.lang.String.class,javafx.scene.control.TitledPane.class},
                   name={"asTitleSelectable","asTitledPaneSelectable"})
public class AccordionWrap<CONTROL extends javafx.scene.control.Accordion>
extends ControlWrap<CONTROL>
    Wrapper for Accordion control. There are two ways to deal with the accordion: though Selectable control interface or by finding an TitledPane (such as through TitledPaneDock) and causing that to expand or collapse. Please see sample code for more info: AccordionSample
    See Also:
    AccordionDock, TitledPaneDock
